TopicTitle: Ksp keeps crashing while on loading screen

Articles.Content:
Hi there. Have you the latest drivers for your graphics card? Have you recently updated to Windows 10?

Also I had a similar problem when I first installed KSP and clicking "run as administrator " fixed it for me. Maybe worth a try.

Did it just start happening? Did KSP ever run properly before? Do other games run?

This doesn't mean much:  Version:  Direct3D 9.0c [nvd3dumx.dll 10.18.13.6871] to me but yeah, get latest drivers from Nvidia. Do not let Windows install video drivers!

Edited April 17, 2017 by Kerbital

It just started happening when i installed more than 20 mods and never crashed before. Also when I run the game as a read-only it reduces the chance of the game crashing but it still crashes after about 15 minutes. When I remove each mod one by one, the crashing never goes away. Other games I have-minecraft, universe sandbox- don't crash

I'll try updating the graphics driver and clicking run as administrator when i get the chance.

Edited April 17, 2017 by Aniruddh

You are running out of physical memory which is causing an access violation

Spoiler

Error occurred at 2017-04-12_202148.
C:\Users\Owner\Documents\KSP_Stock\KSP_x64.exe, run by Owner.
76% memory in use.
8065 MB physical memory [1883 MB free].
11649 MB paging file [1912 MB free].
134217728 MB user address space [134211437 MB free].
Write to location 9a63e4f0 caused an access violation.

You have a pagefile that is 11 gigs () and about 1.5 gigs left out of 8 gigs physical ram

This is the problem

2 solutions: 1- get more physical ram or 2- reduce the amount of mods you are using

17 hours ago, Aniruddh said:

It just started happening when i installed more than 20 mods and never crashed before. Also when I run the game as a read-only it reduces the chance of the game crashing but it still crashes after about 15 minutes. When I remove each mod one by one, the crashing never goes away. Other games I have-minecraft, universe sandbox- don't crash

I'll try updating the graphics driver and clicking run as administrator when i get the chance.

20 mods? Depending on what you computer is, don't install too many mods. Install the essentials only. Update your drivers, and if that doesn't work, try

-force-opengl (I did it with 30, and it stopped crashing)
If updated video drivers don't help then what DoctorDavinci said might be true. Having page file larger than your physical RAM is never a good thing.
